{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N6sMGMvTKZrjZNWzXvpURC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-28\n     2→\n     3→## Session 51 — Sprint Complete, No-Op #35\n     4→\n     5→**Date:** 2026-03-28\n     6→**Session:** 51\n     7→**Sprint status:** COMPLETE — 74/74 stories done, 17/17 epics done\n     8→**Productive work this session:** None. State corruption fix only.\n     9→\n    10→---\n    11→\n    12→## Sprint Summary\n    13→\n    14→| Metric | Value |\n    15→|--------|-------|\n    16→| Total stories | 74 |\n    17→| Stories done | 74 |\n    18→| Total epics | 17 |\n    19→| Epics done | 17 |\n    20→| Sprint completed at | Session 30 |\n    21→| No-op sessions since completion | 35 (sessions 17-51) |\n    22→\n    23→## The Recurring Bug\n    24→\n    25→Every session since session 17, Ralph's stale in-memory state overwrites `sprint-state.json`, reverting stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 from `done` to `review` and epic-16 from `done` to `backlog`. Each session detects the regression, fixes it, logs it, and exits. This is the 35th consecutive occurrence.\n    26→\n    27→**Root cause:** Ralph loads state at startup, holds it in memory, and writes it back on each loop iteration. The in-memory snapshot predates the completion of stories 16-5 through 16-8. The `registerStory` guard (session 22) prevents new phantom stories but does not prevent status reversion of existing stories.\n    28→\n    29→**Evidence from `ralph/status.json`:**\n    30→- `stories_completed: 70` (should be 74)\n    31→- `stories_remaining: 4` (should be 0)\n    32→- Ralph still believes 4 stories are incomplete\n    33→\n    34→**Fix deployed each session:** Restore 4 stories to `done`, set epic-16 to `done`, update totals from 70 to 74. Sometimes also remove `1-1-foo` phantom.\n    35→\n    36→## Cost Analysis\n    37→\n    38→### Cumulative Sprint Cost\n    39→\n    40→| Metric | Value |\n    41→|--------|-------|\n    42→| Total API-equivalent cost | $716.85 |\n    43→| Total API calls | 5,268 |\n    44→| Average cost per story | $3.54 |\n    45→| Total tokens (all types) | ~299.2M |\n    46→\n    47→### Cost Breakdown by Token Type\n    48→\n    49→| Type | Tokens | Cost | % |\n    50→|------|--------|------|---|\n    51→| Cache reads | 288,997,497 | $433.50 | 60% |\n    52→| Cache writes | 9,137,995 | $171.34 | 24% |\n    53→| Output | 1,491,020 | $111.83 | 16% |\n    54→| Input | 12,796 | $0.19 | 0% |\n    55→\n    56→### Cost by Phase\n    57→\n    58→| Phase | Calls | Cost | % |\n    59→|-------|-------|------|---|\n    60→| verify | 3,077 | $388.63 | 54.2% |\n    61→| orchestrator | 714 | $148.96 | 20.8% |\n    62→| retro | 539 | $75.87 | 10.6% |\n    63→| code-review | 323 | $36.74 | 5.1% |\n    64→| create-story | 344 | $36.58 | 5.1% |\n    65→| dev-story | 271 | $30.07 | 4.2% |\n    66→\n    67→### Cost Delta Since Last Report\n    68→\n    69→| Metric | Previous (session 50) | Current (session 51) | Delta |\n    70→|--------|----------------------|---------------------|-------|\n    71→| Total cost | $714.12 | $716.85 | +$2.73 |\n    72→| Total calls | 5,250 | 5,268 | +18 |\n    73→| verify phase | $387.16 | $388.63 | +$1.47 |\n    74→| orchestrator phase | $148.19 | $148.96 | +$0.77 |\n    75→| retro phase | $75.38 | $75.87 | +$0.49 |\n    76→\n    77→### Waste Estimate\n    78→\n    79→Sessions 17-51 (35 no-op sessions) each cost approximately $2-3 in tokens for the same fix-and-exit cycle. Estimated total waste from the recurring bug: **~$70-100** (roughly 10-14% of total sprint cost).\n    80→\n    81→The `1-1-foo` phantom story ranks #2 in most expensive stories at $24.25 — entirely wasted on a non-existent story that Ralph repeatedly injects.\n    82→\n    83→## What Went Well (Sprint Overall)\n    84→\n    85→- All 74 stories across 17 epics were completed by session 30\n    86→- Average cost per real story ($3.54) is reasonable for autonomous execution\n    87→- The `registerStory` guard partially mitigated phantom story injection\n    88→- Sprint status YAML derived view keeps the canonical status readable\n    89→\n    90→## What Went Wrong\n    91→\n    92→1. **Ralph state reversion bug is unfixed after 35 sessions.** The in-memory state overwrite has never been patched at the source. Each session burns tokens on the same repair.\n    93→2. **Ralph was never stopped.** After sprint completion at session 30, Ralph should have been halted. It was not. 21 additional sessions ran for zero productive output.\n    94→3. **$24.25 wasted on phantom story `1-1-foo`.** Ralph injected a non-existent story repeatedly, and verification cycles ran against it.\n    95→4. **Verification phase consumes 54.2% of total cost.** Disproportionate relative to actual dev work (4.2%). Worth investigating whether verification is over-running.\n    96→\n    97→## Action Items\n    98→\n    99→| # | Action | Priority | Status |\n   100→|---|--------|----------|--------|"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HzBN5LhEwxXYATjSUsV8z2","session_id":"8f8138f8-cfc4-4e69-911d-5410595e0d7d","uuid":"71ef4db3-a4c7-491e-8ee0-8bd042cc0419","timestamp":"2026-03-28T12:05:48.708Z"}
