{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q3eANTPx5dLFS4ZyRHDR7t","type":"tool_result","content":"  3900→\n  3901→## 5. What Went Wrong\n  3902→\n  3903→- **The BATS bug persisted across multiple sessions.** It was first observed during story 16-6 verification and flagged as a P2. It should have been fixed immediately — BATS tests are part of the CI gate and 5 failures is not acceptable to carry.\n  3904→- **Session kill lost state transitions.** The previous session did the hard work (verification) but the easy part (updating sprint-state.json) was lost because proof generation and state update are not atomic.\n  3905→- **40+ no-op sessions before this one.** The Ralph state corruption bug burned an estimated $80-120 across sessions that accomplished nothing.\n  3906→\n  3907→## 6. Lessons Learned\n  3908→\n  3909→### Shell Compatibility Checklist (New)\n  3910→\n  3911→When writing shell scripts for this project:\n  3912→- No `local -A` or `declare -A` (associative arrays) — bash 4+ only\n  3913→- No `mapfile` or `readarray` — bash 4+ only\n  3914→- No `${var,,}` or `${var^^}` (case modification) — bash 4+ only\n  3915→- No `|&` (pipe stderr) — bash 4+ only\n  3916→- No `coproc` — bash 4+ only\n  3917→- Use `grep -qxF` or similar POSIX tools for set-membership checks\n  3918→- Test scripts with `/bin/bash --posix` or explicitly check `${BASH_VERSINFO[0]}`\n  3919→\n  3920→### Atomic State Transitions\n  3921→\n  3922→Proof generation and sprint-state.json updates should be a single atomic operation, or at minimum, the state file should be written first (it is cheap to re-verify if the proof file is missing, but expensive to re-verify if state says \"review\" but proof says ALL_PASS).\n  3923→\n  3924→### Fix Test Failures Immediately\n  3925→\n  3926→Carrying failing tests as \"known issues\" or \"pre-existing failures\" normalizes breakage. The 5 BATS failures should have been fixed the moment they were discovered in session 30, not carried forward to this session.\n  3927→\n  3928→## 7. Action Items\n  3929→\n  3930→| Priority | Action | Status |\n  3931→|----------|--------|--------|\n  3932→| **P0** | Stop Ralph. Sprint is done. | **DONE** (this session) |\n  3933→| **P1** | Add sprint-complete exit condition to Ralph's main loop | CARRY FORWARD |\n  3934→| **P1** | Make proof + state transition atomic (or state-first) | CARRY FORWARD |\n  3935→| **P1** | Attribute the \"unknown\" cost bucket ($220.32, 25.8%) | CARRY FORWARD |\n  3936→| **P2** | Add bash version check or shellcheck enforcement for ralph scripts | CARRY FORWARD |\n  3937→| **P2** | Optimize verification phase cost (53.2% of total) | CARRY FORWARD |\n  3938→| **P2** | Add subagent guideline: capture test output once, grep from capture | CARRY FORWARD |\n  3939→| **P3** | Clean up legacy terms (black.box references) in patches/templates | CARRY FORWARD |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HzBN5LhEwxXYATjSUsV8z2","session_id":"8f8138f8-cfc4-4e69-911d-5410595e0d7d","uuid":"cd5c1f60-a5fe-47b7-b93f-b8764f161dec","timestamp":"2026-03-28T12:06:20.251Z"}
