{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FxDY1fSiSt5tgeGJYLSM9d","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KDXQuJLbTeeq5JSbXHd6z2","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md","old_string":"| **P3** | Clean up legacy terms (black.box references) in patches/templates | CARRY FORWARD |","new_string":"| **P3** | Clean up legacy terms (black.box references) in patches/templates | CARRY FORWARD |\n\n---\n\n## Session — Cleanup & Sprint Closure (2026-03-28T16:00Z)\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-28\n**Sprint status:** COMPLETE — 74/74 stories done, 17/17 epics done, ALL_DONE\n**Productive work this session:** Status desync fix, sprint closure confirmation\n\n---\n\n## 1. Session Summary\n\nThis was a short cleanup session. No code was written. The work consisted of:\n\n- Stories 16-7 and 16-8 had been fully implemented, code-reviewed, and verified (ALL_PASS) in the previous session (session 31), but `sprint-state.json` was not updated to reflect `done` status. This session corrected the status entries.\n- Confirmed all 74 stories across 16 epics (plus epic-0) are now `done` in `sprint-state.json`.\n- Confirmed all verification proofs exist and are valid.\n- Sprint is fully complete: ALL_DONE.\n\n**Outcome:** Sprint closure achieved. The entire backlog of 74 stories across 17 epics is done.\n\n## 2. Issues Analysis\n\nIssues from the session issues log cover stories 16-5 through 16-8 (all from the previous session's subagent runs):\n\n### Code Review Findings\n\n| Story | HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW | Sent Back |\n|-------|------|--------|-----|-----------|\n| 16-5 (harness-run dispatch) | 0 | 3 (all fixed) | 2 (not fixed) | No |\n| 16-6 (create-story tier criteria) | 1 (fixed) | 2 (no fix needed) | 1 | No |\n| 16-7 (knowledge & enforcement docs) | 0 | 4 (all fixed) | 2 (not fixed, out of scope) | No |\n| 16-8 (update all tests) | 0 | 0 | 3 (not fixed) | No |\n\n**Total bugs found and fixed:** 1 HIGH, 9 MEDIUM. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues were resolved during the code review phase before verification. No stories were sent back for re-development.\n\n**Unfixed LOW items (carried forward):**\n- Routing table vs section order mismatch in harness-run.md\n- String-matching test brittleness (inherent to testing prompt files)\n- Test count docs drift\n- Legacy terms in patches/AGENTS.md, patches/retro/enforcement.md, src/templates/verify-prompt.ts (out of scope)\n- classifyTier barrel re-export not tested through index.ts\n- Story line references will drift\n- No explicit runtime>test priority test in classifyTier\n\n### Verification Results\n\nAll 4 stories passed verification with perfect scores:\n- 16-5: ALL_PASS (7/7 ACs)\n- 16-6: ALL_PASS (10/10 ACs)\n- 16-7: ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs)\n- 16-8: ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs)\n\n**Test count:** 4,020 tests passing. Coverage: 96.85% overall, all 158 files above 80% floor.\n\n### Subagent Token Efficiency\n\n| Story Phase | Tool Calls | Notes |\n|-------------|-----------|-------|\n| 16-5 review | 27 | Minimal redundancy |\n| 16-5 verify | 15 | npm test run twice (could combine) |\n| 16-6 review | 19 | Story test file run 3 times |\n| 16-6 verify | 15 | Minimal redundancy |\n| 16-7 review | 22 | One redundant read, two grep passes could combine |\n| 16-7 verify | 16 | npm test run twice |\n| 16-8 review | 18 | No redundancy |\n| 16-8 verify | 14 | npm test run twice |\n| **Total** | **146** | |\n\nRecurring pattern: subagents run `npm test` twice (once for full output, once filtered). This is a minor inefficiency that could be addressed by capturing output once and grepping from the capture.\n\n## 3. Cost Analysis\n\n### Cumulative Sprint Cost\n\n| Metric | Previous Session | Current | Delta |\n|--------|-----------------|---------|-------|\n| Total API-equivalent cost | ~$840 (est.) | $858.23 | +~$18 |\n| Total API calls | ~6,100 (est.) | 6,244 | +~144 |\n| Average cost per story | — | $4.02 (158 entries, incl. phantom) | — |\n\n### Current Cost Breakdown\n\n| Type | Tokens | Cost | % |\n|------|--------|------|---|\n| Cache reads | 333.8M | $500.72 | 58% |\n| Cache writes | 11.9M | $223.50 | 26% |\n| Output | 1.78M | $133.79 | 16% |\n| Input | 14.6K | $0.22 | 0% |\n\n### Cost by Phase\n\n| Phase | Calls | Cost | % |\n|-------|-------|------|---|\n| verify | 3,655 | $457.21 | 53.3% |\n| orchestrator | 864 | $190.55 | 22.2% |\n| retro | 736 | $100.89 | 11.8% |\n| code-review | 370 | $42.45 | 4.9% |\n| create-story | 348 | $37.05 | 4.3% |\n| dev-story | 271 | $30.07 | 3.5% |\n\n### Waste Analysis\n\n- **\"unknown\" bucket:** $222.57 (25.9%) — the single largest cost item. This is unattributed spend, likely from orchestrator overhead, ralph loop iterations, and no-op sessions. Attributing this remains a P1 action item.\n- **`1-1-foo` phantom story:** $24.35 (2.8%) — entirely wasted on a non-existent story.\n- **No-op sessions (est. 38+):** ~$80-120 wasted on repeated state-fix cycles.\n- **Verification phase:** $457.21 (53.3%) — still disproportionate vs dev-story ($30.07, 3.5%). Ratio is ~15:1 verify-to-dev.\n- **Estimated real cost per story** (excluding waste): If we subtract ~$250 in waste (unknown + phantom + no-ops), real cost is ~$608 for 74 stories = **~$8.22/story** for the full pipeline (create-story + dev + review + verify + retro).\n\n## 4. What Went Well\n\n- **Sprint is complete.** 74 stories, 17 epics, zero failures, zero blocked. Every story passed verification.\n- **Code review caught real bugs.** 1 HIGH and 9 MEDIUM bugs were caught and fixed before verification, preventing rework.\n- **Verification was thorough.** 41/41 ACs passed across the final 4 stories. Coverage remained at 96.85%.\n- **This session was short and focused.** Identified the desync, fixed it, confirmed closure. No unnecessary work.\n- **Bash 3.x compat fix** from previous session (commit `16c54aa`) resolved the BATS failures that had been carried as known issues.\n\n## 5. What Went Wrong\n\n- **Status desync between sprint-state.json and actual completion.** Stories 16-7 and 16-8 were fully implemented, reviewed, and verified in the previous session, but sprint-state.json was not updated. The previous session did the hard work but failed to record it. This is the same \"non-atomic state transition\" issue identified in the previous retro.\n- **Root cause is unchanged:** proof generation and state updates are two separate steps. If the session ends (or Ralph overwrites state) between them, the state file becomes inconsistent with reality.\n- **The \"unknown\" cost bucket ($222.57) remains unattributed.** At 25.9% of total cost, this is the biggest line item and we still do not know what it is.\n\n## 6. Lessons Learned\n\n### State Transitions Must Be Atomic (Reinforced)\n\nThis is the second consecutive session identifying this problem. The pattern is clear: verification produces a proof document, but the sprint-state.json update is a separate step that can be lost. The fix is straightforward — update state immediately after proof generation within the same operation, or make state-first (cheap to re-verify if proof is missing).\n\n### Sprint Completion Needs a Definition of Done\n\nThe sprint was \"done\" in terms of all stories passing verification, but the state file did not reflect this. There needs to be a single authoritative check: if all proof documents exist and all ACs pass, the state file should be reconciled automatically. The existing `state-reconciliation-on-session-start` (story 11-3) should cover this, but it did not fire or was not effective.\n\n### Cost Attribution Gaps Persist\n\nOver a quarter of total spend is unattributed. Without knowing what \"unknown\" represents, cost optimization is guesswork. This should be a P1 fix for the next sprint.\n\n## 7. Action Items\n\n| Priority | Action | Status |\n|----------|--------|--------|\n| **P0** | Sprint is done. No more execution needed. | **DONE** |\n| **P1** | Make proof + state transition atomic (or state-first) | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P1** | Attribute the \"unknown\" cost bucket ($222.57, 25.9%) | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P1** | Add sprint-complete exit condition to Ralph's main loop | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P1** | Verify state-reconciliation (story 11-3) fires on session start and actually reconciles | NEW |\n| **P2** | Optimize verification phase cost (53.3% of total, 15:1 ratio vs dev) | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Add subagent guideline: capture test output once, grep from capture | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Add bash version check or shellcheck enforcement for ralph scripts | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P3** | Clean up legacy terms (black.box references) in patches/templates | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story references from tracking data | CARRY FORWARD |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":996,"cache_read_input_tokens":41907,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":996,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HzBN5LhEwxXYATjSUsV8z2","session_id":"8f8138f8-cfc4-4e69-911d-5410595e0d7d","uuid":"086e67f6-4bd3-4e3a-a9b8-d7f4607e0f1e"}
